A SHOOTING incident in Rosslyn, Tshwane, has left one person dead and another injured. According to Gauteng police spokesman Lieutenant-Colonel Mavela Masondo, the incident happened on Wednesday, 27 July, at around 11.40am. Police have opened a case of murder and attempted murder. Masondo said police are searching for the suspects following a shooting incident at a petrol station in Rosslyn where one person died at the scene and the petrol attendant sustained injuries. “The suspects are said to be driving a white Toyota Etios hatchback. “It is reported that the deceased, who is 52 years old, had stopped at the petrol station when he was accosted by two armed suspects who fired shots at him with rifles. “A petrol attendant sustained injuries after he was hit by bullets in his hand and abdomen,” said Masondo. He said the motive for the shooting cannot be confirmed at this stage. He said police are appealing to anyone who might have information that can help in the investigation or assist in the apprehension of the suspects to please call the nearest police station or CrimeStop on 08600 10111.